snippet.textDisplay:
Once upon a time, a battle was had between tow opposing factions with 10,000 soldiers on each side. In the end, you approach the battle field and find 1 person left standing. 
Was he the best fighter or the best coward?
The truth is, he was most likely neither. All we can know for sure is that he lived to fight another day, and the story that he tells will be the one that you hear.

What story will you pass on?
Why?
